From fed4163d5cb6a07d425e9133dad79ba04f7b8f34 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Vadim Pasternak <vadimp@nvidia.com>
Date: Sun, 24 May 2026 19:12:12 +0300
Subject: [PATCH 2/3] platform/mellanox: nvsw-bmc: Add system control and
 monitoring driver

Add BMC-side CPLD/FPGA driver for Nvidia switches (HID162/176/177/180/181/
189/191/193), sharing nvsw-core infrastructure with the host drivers.

The driver allows system control and monitoring through CPLD/FPGA devices
from Baseboard Management Controller SoC, including hotplug events, resets,
reset cause reports, mux selection, GP registers, LED and FAN control.

Document new mlxreg-io sysfs attributes exposed on BMC platforms under the
I2C-attached CPLD device path.

Signed-off-by: Aaron Komisar <akomisar@nvidia.com>
Reviewed-by: Vadim Pasternak <vadimp@nvidia.com>
